Anyways, I am writing this to inquire as to what had happened at the Ry'Gorr fort last night.  As an officer of Unyielding Power, I want to make sure that all of our members have acted in a classy, dignified manner as we have only come to expect from them (myself included).  I was not present in game last night, but your post mentioned some kind of &quot;zone arguement&quot;....This inquiry may in fact not be needed, but I feel the need to look into these matters for the integrity of Unyielding Power and our members.  I think you all would do the same.<br><br>I appreciate the space you have given me for this post, and I hope to see you all in game in the future.  <br><br>Regards,<br><br>Darlok<br>Officer Unyielding Power<br><br><br>Darlok has been slain by a Goblin Whelp.....Loading, Please Wait. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/usixpence6.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sixpence6</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.webdeveloper.com/animations/bnifiles/muziek3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bard Officer</span><br>  Posts: 639<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/12/02 10:13:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=476.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gucomics.keenspace.com/images/bard_side.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RyGorr Fort Inquiry</span><hr size=1> Well met Darlok<br>And thank you for visiting us friend.<br>I believe that the whole incident was a mere Tiff nothing more.<br>We were pulling from the fort as I stated,A mixed group containing various Guilds;<br>(Tempest of fate,Epic Heroes &amp; another..my memory at 3 am is dubious at best).<br>I noticed that a group of your guild had set about pulling the Chief &amp; thought ok,fair play as the fort seems to be open season at the best of times regarding camps etc..&amp; there were plenty of Monsters to go round, no problem there.<br>The next thing I know up pops an Elite &amp; takes umbrage to me Mezzing his chum, ouch..luckily it holds &amp; we manage to finish the Lego &amp; then his bigger brother.<br>I think that the problem stemmed from members of our group believing that the sudden appearance (we all know they like to &quot;Appear&quot; with the wall bug) of the Elite was caused by your Guild's Attack on the Chief &amp; then the Chat went along the lines of:<br><br>&quot;Well you are all far too young to take the chief, so we did &amp; should the avengers spawn  you will all die etc etc..&quot; (In all honesty this may be inaccurate as I was twisting like a Loon &amp; struggling to keep my eyes open by this point).<br><br>Now we are all  experienced players &amp; as anyone who has hunted the fort is aware the Avengers do not always spawn..fair enough I thought maybe they are merely warning us about the dreaded...<br><br>'We have come to avenge the killing of the Ry'gorr chief'. <br>(Which nobody really needs to hear especially at No Mana/Cigarretes &amp; Half Health).<br><br>All in all it was your usual confused post coffee/Wee hours spat nothing more friend.<br>No hard feelings either way I hope &amp; safe trails to you &amp; Yours.<br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=89090">Six</a><br> <a href="http://www.epic-heroes.com"target="_blank">Epic Heroes</a><br><a href="http://www.eqdiva.com"target="_blank">Singer's haven</a><br>"Sooner a kindly Wolverine than a faithful Minstrel.." R.Hobb.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/usixpence6.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sixpence6</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.webdeveloper.com/animations/bnifiles/muziek3.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/12/02 10:45:34 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/udarlokrulez.show